    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Durham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince, Haiti</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received February 26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 47.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch, No. 29, Diplomatic series, in which you refer to my No. 36, January 7,
                    and repeat the Department’s instructions concerning the question of asylum in
                    Haiti.</p>
                <p>The previous instructions of the Department were so clear to me at the time that
                    I declined to entertain the applications. The two applicants to whom I refer in
                    my dispatch were afterwards received at the French legation and granted asylum
                    there.</p>
                <p>No refugees have been received at either the legation or my residence during my
                    incumbency here.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John S. Durham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
